comments.body:
The `.image` units were created because not all flows that required the image to be available locally supported pull as part of the command. Specifically, it was image based volumes. So, while pulling the image via the `.container` can workaround this specific issue, I think we should address this in the `.image` units.

I would prefer to have a pull policy in the `podman pull` command first and only then implement the Quadlet key for it as it will be much cleaner. But, as always, it's about how long will it take.

@Luap99 WDYT? Can we add this to pull in a simple way? Will that also require changing the implementation of `run` (because it will be able to pass the flag to the pull request)?
